%% How a closure captures drives which Fn* trait it implements.
flowchart TD
    Q{What does the closure<br/>do with captured values?}
    Q -->|only reads them| Fn[Fn<br/>&self · callable many times]
    Q -->|mutates them| FnMut[FnMut<br/>&mut self · still callable many times]
    Q -->|consumes them<br/>move + drop| FnOnce[FnOnce<br/>self · callable exactly once]

    Fn -->|add move||Move1[move || reads<br/>still Fn, owns captures]
    FnMut -->|add move||Move2[move || mutates<br/>still FnMut, owns captures]
    FnOnce -->|add move||Move3[move || consumes<br/>still FnOnce]

    note1[move keyword says 'take ownership of captures'.<br/>It does NOT change which Fn* trait you implement —<br/>it changes WHAT you own.]
    Move1 -.-> note1
